WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.951 --> 00:00:09.246
[♪ epic theme music playing]

2
00:01:55.352 --> 00:01:57.354
- [insects chirring]
- [birdsong]

3
00:02:11.868 --> 00:02:14.079
[man shouting indistinctly]

4
00:02:15.455 --> 00:02:17.206
Keep going!

5
00:02:17.207 --> 00:02:19.208
Bring it on down!

6
00:02:19.209 --> 00:02:20.543
- That's it!
- Come on!

7
00:02:20.544 --> 00:02:22.044
- Keep moving!
- Back into it.

8
00:02:22.045 --> 00:02:24.714
[chickens bocking]

9
00:02:24.715 --> 00:02:26.132
Three more in here.

10
00:02:26.133 --> 00:02:28.759
- [crowd shouting]
- [banging]

11
00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:30.721
- Three more in there.
- [animals bleating]

12
00:02:31.763 --> 00:02:32.889
You. go with them!

13
00:02:33.932 --> 00:02:35.392
Two more in here.

14
00:02:36.310 --> 00:02:38.312
[indistinct chatter continues]

15
00:02:39.646 --> 00:02:40.939
Two more in here.

16
00:02:42.733 --> 00:02:44.401
[giving orders]

17
00:02:48.572 --> 00:02:50.574
You three. in this one.

18
00:02:52.409 --> 00:02:53.660
Oh. please. please.

19
00:02:54.870 --> 00:02:57.079
Our home. it's...
it's already crowded.

20
00:02:57.080 --> 00:02:59.749
There's 15.000 of us.

21
00:02:59.750 --> 00:03:01.168
Be glad you only got three.

22
00:03:04.254 --> 00:03:06.923
- Maybe crowded ain't so bad.
- Mind yourself.

23
00:03:08.175 --> 00:03:10.926
You don't like it.
go and carp to Lord Ormund.

24
00:03:10.927 --> 00:03:12.262
See what good it does you.

25
00:03:18.602 --> 00:03:20.604
[townsfolk chattering]

26
00:03:25.317 --> 00:03:29.487
It is only regarding
the lodging situation. my lord.

27
00:03:29.488 --> 00:03:32.114
You are unhappy with
your lodgings. Lord Footly?

28
00:03:32.115 --> 00:03:34.450
It is only that we are very fond
of our ancestral home.

29
00:03:34.451 --> 00:03:36.411
You are sleeping
in our bedchamber.

30
00:03:37.245 --> 00:03:39.664
You bent the knee to the pretender.
Rhaenyra Targaryen.

31
00:03:39.665 --> 00:03:41.666
did you not. Lady Footly?

32
00:03:41.667 --> 00:03:43.459
We did.

33
00:03:43.460 --> 00:03:44.877
Then mayhaps
I should remind you

34
00:03:44.878 --> 00:03:46.837
that the wage of treason
is death.

35
00:03:46.838 --> 00:03:48.381
We do not seek conflict.
my lord.

36
00:03:48.382 --> 00:03:50.800
- [groaning]
- Tumbleton has no battlements.

37
00:03:50.801 --> 00:03:52.510
Our people know only trade.

38
00:03:52.511 --> 00:03:55.346
We never thought to see war.

39
00:03:55.347 --> 00:03:57.306
So. you swore to her
out of fear.

40
00:03:57.307 --> 00:03:59.893
We swore because
she is the queen.

41
00:04:03.188 --> 00:04:04.690
Is she?

42
00:04:14.908 --> 00:04:17.160
Or is she a bitch
with a dragon?

43
00:04:18.161 --> 00:04:19.705
[water sloshing]

44
00:04:21.373 --> 00:04:23.666
My purpose is to restore
the rightful line

45
00:04:23.667 --> 00:04:24.918
to the Iron Throne.

46
00:04:26.002 --> 00:04:28.505
It follows from that
that I must be well rested.

47
00:04:30.006 --> 00:04:34.344
It follows from that that I must have
acceptable lodgings.

48
00:04:35.262 --> 00:04:38.597
I will ensure that my men
remain on their best behavior

49
00:04:38.598 --> 00:04:40.183
whilst in your town.

50
00:04:42.227 --> 00:04:44.396
Provided. of course...
[sighs]

51
00:04:46.606 --> 00:04:48.858
...that you remain on yours.

52
00:04:48.859 --> 00:04:50.193
See them out.

53
00:04:52.779 --> 00:04:54.156
[Lady Footly] Don't.

54
00:04:54.740 --> 00:04:56.240
When dealing with those
beneath you.

55
00:04:56.241 --> 00:04:58.284
you must be fair. but firm.

56
00:04:58.285 --> 00:04:59.703
Yes. sire.

57
00:05:02.789 --> 00:05:04.039
My prince.

58
00:05:04.040 --> 00:05:06.375
My lord. a raven
from Storm's End

59
00:05:06.376 --> 00:05:09.087
carrying more excuses
from Lord Borros Baratheon.

60
00:05:16.344 --> 00:05:19.013
That lackwit sealed a marriage pact
between Prince Aemond

61
00:05:19.014 --> 00:05:21.974
and one of his horse-faced
daughters.

62
00:05:21.975 --> 00:05:23.934
And yet. where is he now?

63
00:05:23.935 --> 00:05:26.061
Send another raven
that he can understand.

64
00:05:26.062 --> 00:05:28.565
This one mayhaps with drawings
rather than letters.

65
00:05:34.362 --> 00:05:36.156
What word from Harrenhal?

66
00:05:38.366 --> 00:05:42.579
[Roxton] If Vhagar does not come.
our defenses will not hold.

67
00:05:48.376 --> 00:05:50.212
Do not be disheartened.
Daeron.

68
00:05:51.922 --> 00:05:53.590
Your brother will join us soon.

69
00:05:58.595 --> 00:06:01.138
[Rhaenyra]
<i>Why seize Tumbleton?</i>

70
00:06:01.139 --> 00:06:04.183
It's no stronghold.
It's a market town.

71
00:06:04.184 --> 00:06:07.436
Its lord is meek.
Its walls are poorly defended.

72
00:06:07.437 --> 00:06:09.814
Hightower may as well
paint a rondel on his chest.

73
00:06:09.815 --> 00:06:10.816
Why?

74
00:06:11.942 --> 00:06:14.110
Does he mean to somehow
win their support?

75
00:06:16.196 --> 00:06:19.114
He dares me
to rain fire down on a seat

76
00:06:19.115 --> 00:06:21.283
that raised my banner.

77
00:06:21.284 --> 00:06:23.661
And the realm would name me
"Maegor Returned."

78
00:06:23.662 --> 00:06:25.621
They'd rise up against me.

79
00:06:25.622 --> 00:06:28.290
And the same gods
who delivered me to the throne

80
00:06:28.291 --> 00:06:29.667
would rightly cast me down.

81
00:06:29.668 --> 00:06:32.378
[Orwyle] If I may.

82
00:06:32.379 --> 00:06:34.296
Your Grace.
Prince Daemon's river host

83
00:06:34.297 --> 00:06:36.632
marches on King's Landing.

84
00:06:36.633 --> 00:06:39.009
Tumbleton is not much further.

85
00:06:39.010 --> 00:06:41.387
If his men were
to go there instead...

86
00:06:41.388 --> 00:06:44.390
Mm. it would not be bloodless.

87
00:06:44.391 --> 00:06:47.477
but it would be far more
merciful than sending dragons.

88
00:06:49.479 --> 00:06:51.146
We march on the town

89
00:06:51.147 --> 00:06:53.650
and root out the Hightowers
house to house.

90
00:06:55.652 --> 00:06:57.403
It's a good scheme.

91
00:06:57.404 --> 00:06:59.030
Send orders to Lord Tully.

92
00:07:00.991 --> 00:07:02.367
Uh. Orwyle?

93
00:07:03.952 --> 00:07:07.247
For as long as you remain
loyal and useful...

94
00:07:08.415 --> 00:07:10.499
you may take your place
at my council

95
00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:12.335
and retain the title
of Grand Maester.

96
00:07:16.214 --> 00:07:18.173
The castle's ravens
remain your charge.

97
00:07:18.174 --> 00:07:20.760
but the Lady Mysaria should be
kept informed of the comings and goings.

98
00:07:21.720 --> 00:07:22.721
Ah.

99
00:07:23.680 --> 00:07:26.683
Relics of a dead regime.

100
00:07:27.851 --> 00:07:29.518
Mm.

101
00:07:29.519 --> 00:07:32.271
It will take the Rivermen weeks
to reach Tumbleton.

102
00:07:32.272 --> 00:07:34.773
Let us send a dragon
to keep vigil.

103
00:07:34.774 --> 00:07:37.234
Ormund may have
the town under siege.

104
00:07:37.235 --> 00:07:40.279
but he shall not leave
except I remove him.

105
00:07:40.280 --> 00:07:45.075
In the meantime. we have.
uh. urgent matters at home.

106
00:07:45.076 --> 00:07:47.578
We have secured
some small store of oil

107
00:07:47.579 --> 00:07:49.372
- for the markets. but...
- Where is the Hand?

108
00:07:51.333 --> 00:07:54.210
- Gods. this council's thin.
- [chalice scraping]

109
00:07:58.715 --> 00:08:00.383
Name a Master of Coin.

110
00:08:01.384 --> 00:08:04.970
The people will soon discover
our lacking resources.

111
00:08:04.971 --> 00:08:07.015
They can blame him.

112
00:08:11.436 --> 00:08:14.063
Investigate
Ser Torrhen Manderly.

113
00:08:14.064 --> 00:08:15.898
He's intrigued me.

114
00:08:15.899 --> 00:08:18.735
If he's fit. let the gold
be his concern as well as Daemon's.

115
00:08:20.403 --> 00:08:22.906
Mine shall be
Ormund Hightower.

116
00:08:26.576 --> 00:08:28.327
I know him as well as you.

117
00:08:28.328 --> 00:08:30.413
[chuckles] I... I doubt that.

118
00:08:31.414 --> 00:08:34.250
Viserys warded your son to him.
I've never met the man.

119
00:08:35.585 --> 00:08:39.922
I knew him very little.
a long time ago.

120
00:08:39.923 --> 00:08:42.800
After my father took me to court.
I rarely saw Oldtown.

121
00:08:42.801 --> 00:08:44.135
Tell me what you do know.

122
00:08:48.181 --> 00:08:49.515
[clicking tongue]

123
00:08:49.516 --> 00:08:51.935
He sees himself as a scholar.

124
00:08:53.061 --> 00:08:54.937
He studies the histories.

125
00:08:54.938 --> 00:08:58.190
he collects tapestries.
writes ballads.

126
00:08:58.191 --> 00:09:00.151
despises the ignorant
and uncouth.

127
00:09:01.569 --> 00:09:03.445
When we were young.
Gwayne thought him cruel.

128
00:09:03.446 --> 00:09:05.781
but Gwayne thought that of many.

129
00:09:05.782 --> 00:09:07.117
How is he with Daeron?

130
00:09:09.494 --> 00:09:11.704
Fatherly. I'm told.

131
00:09:11.705 --> 00:09:13.832
Daeron was only a babe
when he took him to ward.

132
00:09:14.833 --> 00:09:16.459
[Helaena]
What is it?

133
00:09:17.210 --> 00:09:18.794
Oh. look at this.

134
00:09:18.795 --> 00:09:21.965
Did it pain you to have
to send your child away?

135
00:09:26.636 --> 00:09:28.346
It was my choice.

136
00:09:29.305 --> 00:09:30.306
Why?

137
00:09:31.516 --> 00:09:32.809
[sighs]

138
00:09:34.477 --> 00:09:38.690
I bore Viserys
three Targaryens.

139
00:09:40.191 --> 00:09:41.985
But with the last. my last...

140
00:09:43.194 --> 00:09:45.155
I wanted him to be a Hightower.

141
00:09:47.073 --> 00:09:49.158
In truth. I'm glad
I waged that battle.

142
00:09:49.159 --> 00:09:51.327
seeing now what came
of our other sons.

143
00:09:51.870 --> 00:09:55.331
Perhaps sending Daeron away
was my truest act of motherhood.

144
00:09:58.251 --> 00:09:59.877
Though I do not know
now what fate

145
00:09:59.878 --> 00:10:01.379
that choice has consigned him.

146
00:10:09.512 --> 00:10:11.765
You know I would
have spared him.

147
00:10:21.566 --> 00:10:24.027
He has a sensitivity
to odors.

148
00:10:25.820 --> 00:10:26.863
Ormund.

149
00:10:28.573 --> 00:10:29.908
A very strong one.

150
00:10:32.660 --> 00:10:35.037
My Lord Hand.
the queen has requested

151
00:10:35.038 --> 00:10:36.872
your presence
at her small council.

152
00:10:36.873 --> 00:10:39.583
I'm her Hand.
not her mouth.

153
00:10:39.584 --> 00:10:41.877
Leave the talking to those
who relish it.

154
00:10:41.878 --> 00:10:43.378
Shall I return
with this message?

155
00:10:43.379 --> 00:10:44.838
That you refuse the queen?

156
00:10:44.839 --> 00:10:47.549
Rather that I serve
more effectively.

157
00:10:47.550 --> 00:10:50.219
Her strength lies
in dragons now.

158
00:10:50.220 --> 00:10:52.388
She has less need
of a man of the sea.

159
00:10:54.599 --> 00:10:57.726
But my son shall attend her
in my stead.

160
00:10:57.727 --> 00:10:59.395
You certainly look the part.

161
00:11:00.897 --> 00:11:03.023
I am not a creature
of the court.

162
00:11:03.024 --> 00:11:04.775
I don't know what I'm doing.

163
00:11:04.776 --> 00:11:07.112
There is great opportunity
for you there.

164
00:11:08.780 --> 00:11:10.864
I cannot give you legitimacy.

165
00:11:10.865 --> 00:11:13.409
but I can give you the chance
to better yourself.

166
00:11:18.414 --> 00:11:22.001
Anger is not something that can
be ended with a blade. my lord.

167
00:11:26.589 --> 00:11:27.799
[soldier] Move out!

168
00:11:29.175 --> 00:11:31.177
[horses neighing]

169
00:11:36.975 --> 00:11:39.143
[horse neighing]

170
00:11:39.144 --> 00:11:40.311
Come on!

171
00:11:46.109 --> 00:11:47.485
[grunting]

172
00:11:58.788 --> 00:12:01.791
[♪ somber music playing]

173
00:12:36.326 --> 00:12:38.244
[whispering]
My boy.

174
00:12:39.370 --> 00:12:40.663
I'm here.

175
00:12:42.665 --> 00:12:43.833
I'm here.

176
00:12:47.921 --> 00:12:50.048
It's a penny
to touch the dragon.

177
00:12:52.008 --> 00:12:54.760
Nothing's free
in these woods.

178
00:12:54.761 --> 00:12:57.054
He can sit the saddle
for a halfgroat.

179
00:12:57.055 --> 00:12:58.680
Touch will suffice.

180
00:12:58.681 --> 00:13:00.058
- Mm.
- Thank you.

181
00:13:04.354 --> 00:13:07.105
[clearing throat]
We seek shelter.

182
00:13:07.106 --> 00:13:09.066
Which way to Rook's Rest?

183
00:13:09.067 --> 00:13:11.193
He's got both hands on him.

184
00:13:11.194 --> 00:13:12.528
That's two touches.

185
00:13:30.922 --> 00:13:32.799
What's wrong with your leg?

186
00:13:37.053 --> 00:13:41.140
You can kill a man of the Faith
for a few pennies. if you wish.

187
00:13:42.725 --> 00:13:45.394
Though I doubt the gods
would look kindly upon it.

188
00:13:45.395 --> 00:13:47.479
You don't look like a septon.

189
00:13:47.480 --> 00:13:48.940
[Aegon] He's alive.

190
00:13:53.403 --> 00:13:56.071
I know it.
He's alive. he must be.

191
00:13:56.072 --> 00:13:58.156
- [whispering] Sunfyre.
- There. there. Gregor.

192
00:13:58.157 --> 00:13:59.741
Wake up. Sunfyre.
I'm here.

193
00:13:59.742 --> 00:14:01.910
Let us trouble these
good folk no further. hm?

194
00:14:01.911 --> 00:14:03.996
Wake up. Sunfyre.
I'm here.

195
00:14:03.997 --> 00:14:05.290
Simple.

196
00:14:05.915 --> 00:14:08.583
[speaking High Valyrian]

197
00:14:08.584 --> 00:14:10.460
What's he saying?

198
00:14:10.461 --> 00:14:12.671
[Aegon]
Sunfyre. come back to me.

199
00:14:12.672 --> 00:14:14.881
Wake up. I'm here.
I know you're in there.

200
00:14:14.882 --> 00:14:17.676
We must tarry no longer.
The danger is great.

201
00:14:17.677 --> 00:14:19.970
I am very sorry.

202
00:14:19.971 --> 00:14:22.307
but you must accept
what is before you.

203
00:14:25.101 --> 00:14:26.351
[whispering] Wake up.

204
00:14:26.352 --> 00:14:29.022
You wanted to see him.
you've seen him.

205
00:14:30.315 --> 00:14:32.941
- He's dead.
- No. [sobbing]

206
00:14:32.942 --> 00:14:34.985
Will you stay and rot with him?

207
00:14:34.986 --> 00:14:36.528
[continues sobbing]

208
00:14:36.529 --> 00:14:39.324
Will you get up and live?

209
00:14:48.041 --> 00:14:50.043
- [wind whooshing]
- [horse chortling]

210
00:14:53.629 --> 00:14:56.632
[♪ soft. dramatic music playing]

211
00:15:28.498 --> 00:15:30.665
[distant screeching]

212
00:15:30.666 --> 00:15:32.668
[loud rumbling]

213
00:15:53.189 --> 00:15:55.607
[goat bleating]

214
00:15:55.608 --> 00:15:57.151
[Alys] Are you lost?

215
00:16:02.031 --> 00:16:03.699
Where is the castellan?

216
00:16:06.369 --> 00:16:07.703
Slain.

217
00:16:08.538 --> 00:16:09.914
He who succeeds him then.

218
00:16:11.874 --> 00:16:13.458
Slain.

219
00:16:13.459 --> 00:16:15.420
And the one
who succeeds him as well.

220
00:16:16.879 --> 00:16:18.297
And who are you?

221
00:16:19.215 --> 00:16:21.425
A steward. of a sort.

222
00:16:21.426 --> 00:16:24.052
It's the best you can do
at the moment. [chuckles]

223
00:16:24.053 --> 00:16:25.805
This is the Hand of the King.

224
00:16:26.597 --> 00:16:28.099
We seek the Prince Aemond.

225
00:16:30.059 --> 00:16:32.061
As I'm sure do many.

226
00:16:35.565 --> 00:16:37.899
He was meant
to meet us here.

227
00:16:37.900 --> 00:16:39.151
If you know where he is.

228
00:16:39.152 --> 00:16:41.611
I'd advise you
to be forthcoming.

229
00:16:41.612 --> 00:16:42.822
[Alys scoffs]

230
00:16:45.741 --> 00:16:47.201
He was here.

231
00:16:48.244 --> 00:16:51.496
He seized the castle after
Prince Daemon abandoned it.

232
00:16:51.497 --> 00:16:54.249
but when he learned that
Rhaenyra took King's Landing.

233
00:16:54.250 --> 00:16:57.086
- he and his dragon fled.
- W-When Rhaenyra took King's Landing?

234
00:17:02.967 --> 00:17:04.260
Oh. my.

235
00:17:05.511 --> 00:17:06.971
Oh. you didn't know.

236
00:17:12.935 --> 00:17:14.936
We've scoured the area.
my Lord Hand.

237
00:17:14.937 --> 00:17:17.189
There is sign
of a large dragon nest

238
00:17:17.190 --> 00:17:18.608
but it has been abandoned.

239
00:17:19.609 --> 00:17:22.195
Prince Aemond
may indeed have fled.

240
00:17:32.788 --> 00:17:34.498
King's Landing has fallen.

241
00:17:34.499 --> 00:17:37.709
Aegon is dead. our queens
are both in chains.

242
00:17:37.710 --> 00:17:40.003
and we are here alone

243
00:17:40.004 --> 00:17:42.173
with a meager army
and no dragon.

244
00:17:44.133 --> 00:17:45.968
We have the enemy
just where we want them.

245
00:17:48.513 --> 00:17:50.180
- [sighs]
- Aemond would not desert me.

246
00:17:50.181 --> 00:17:52.975
And yet he's not here. is he?

247
00:17:55.019 --> 00:17:56.771
Let us send a raven
to Tumbleton.

248
00:17:57.688 --> 00:17:59.814
Alert my cousin of this news

249
00:17:59.815 --> 00:18:02.359
and our intent
to join our strength to his.

250
00:18:02.360 --> 00:18:04.194
Ormund is a stiff-necked
windbag.

251
00:18:04.195 --> 00:18:05.654
but he's neither
craven nor stupid.

252
00:18:05.655 --> 00:18:07.990
He will have
some canny plot afoot.

253
00:18:11.327 --> 00:18:12.411
No.

254
00:18:18.167 --> 00:18:21.128
[sword clattering] The game is played.
Ser Criston. and it is lost.

255
00:18:22.129 --> 00:18:24.089
What possible profit
is there in pursuing it?

256
00:18:24.090 --> 00:18:25.383
[scoffs]

257
00:18:28.844 --> 00:18:31.930
You noble ilk conceive this
all a great game. don't you?

258
00:18:31.931 --> 00:18:34.599
To win. to lose.
go home to a feather bed.

259
00:18:34.600 --> 00:18:36.685
[groaning]

260
00:18:36.686 --> 00:18:39.020
I was a foot soldier.
Did you know that?

261
00:18:39.021 --> 00:18:40.522
Steward's son.

262
00:18:40.523 --> 00:18:43.358
All my father had was at
the pleasure of Lord Dondarrion.

263
00:18:43.359 --> 00:18:45.736
When his favor failed.
all we had melted away.

264
00:18:49.031 --> 00:18:50.908
My father died of sorrow.

265
00:18:51.867 --> 00:18:53.869
There is no home
for one like me.

266
00:18:56.539 --> 00:18:58.541
Not while Rhaenyra
sits the throne.

267
00:19:01.877 --> 00:19:03.421
Our task is simple.

268
00:19:04.797 --> 00:19:06.631
Keep the river scum
from reaching King's Landing.

269
00:19:06.632 --> 00:19:08.425
Give Ormund time
to swell his ranks.

270
00:19:08.426 --> 00:19:10.802
Their army is ten times
our size.

271
00:19:10.803 --> 00:19:12.053
Twenty.

272
00:19:12.054 --> 00:19:13.723
But let us attack it...

273
00:19:14.557 --> 00:19:16.559
as the scorpion does the ox.

274
00:19:19.353 --> 00:19:22.897
Let us become wraiths
with fear as our standard.

275
00:19:22.898 --> 00:19:24.441
Strike from the quiet
and the darkness.

276
00:19:24.442 --> 00:19:26.485
Our fight will not be clean.
but it will be pure.

277
00:19:28.321 --> 00:19:29.572
We'll be man-to-man.

278
00:19:32.617 --> 00:19:34.410
And it will be free
from dragons.

279
00:19:39.665 --> 00:19:42.251
- Ser Edgar!
- We'll delay them at most.

280
00:19:44.587 --> 00:19:47.088
- It will not change their course.
- Perhaps not.

281
00:19:47.089 --> 00:19:49.382
But it is as you said.
Ser Gwayne.

282
00:19:49.383 --> 00:19:52.928
We must cling to our honor.
lest we become beasts ourselves.

283
00:19:54.597 --> 00:19:57.642
♪

284
00:20:07.777 --> 00:20:09.487
[rat squeaking]

285
00:20:18.037 --> 00:20:19.537
Who goes there?

286
00:20:19.538 --> 00:20:20.997
Alyn of Hull.

287
00:20:20.998 --> 00:20:22.958
I'll see him. Come.

288
00:20:24.960 --> 00:20:27.128
Your Grace.

289
00:20:27.129 --> 00:20:30.006
Lord Corlys has ridden out
by the Dragon Gate

290
00:20:30.007 --> 00:20:32.510
to hunt the Triarchy raiders
that plague our trade.

291
00:20:34.470 --> 00:20:36.722
He has able men who could
lead that campaign.

292
00:20:38.224 --> 00:20:42.144
While his queen struggles
to restore a broken kingdom.

293
00:20:45.981 --> 00:20:47.983
Your Grace. uh. if I may.

294
00:20:49.527 --> 00:20:52.904
My lord father has lost much

295
00:20:52.905 --> 00:20:55.157
and found himself thwarted.

296
00:20:56.117 --> 00:20:59.995
A fight is mayhaps
what he needs.

297
00:21:02.415 --> 00:21:03.874
Hm.

298
00:21:06.335 --> 00:21:07.670
Oh.

299
00:21:08.713 --> 00:21:10.046
My father's life's work.

300
00:21:10.047 --> 00:21:12.800
a recreation of the seat
of Old Valyria.

301
00:21:14.510 --> 00:21:16.721
A reminder to him.
I think. that. um...

302
00:21:18.806 --> 00:21:20.725
even great dynasties fall.

303
00:21:21.851 --> 00:21:24.270
That the crown should
never rest easy on his head.

304
00:21:26.355 --> 00:21:29.691
There were those who whispered
that my father was weak.

305
00:21:29.692 --> 00:21:32.861
But. um.
seeing through his eyes.

306
00:21:32.862 --> 00:21:34.863
I can only marvel

307
00:21:34.864 --> 00:21:36.866
at how he kept it
all in balance for so long.

308
00:21:38.367 --> 00:21:41.202
Fathers have
a maddening capacity

309
00:21:41.203 --> 00:21:44.038
to at once inspire and incense.

310
00:21:44.039 --> 00:21:46.124
Don't you think?

311
00:21:46.125 --> 00:21:48.543
[rats chittering and scurrying]

312
00:21:48.544 --> 00:21:50.296
Gods. they are incessant.

313
00:21:52.214 --> 00:21:54.759
And thanks to Aegon.
all the rat catchers are dead.

314
00:21:56.218 --> 00:21:58.137
On board ship. we kept cats.

315
00:22:00.556 --> 00:22:03.601
- [bird screeching]
- [Larys] Steel yourself.

316
00:22:04.935 --> 00:22:08.105
We must guard our intents
whilst I quietly

317
00:22:09.648 --> 00:22:12.025
investigate hiring a ship.

318
00:22:12.026 --> 00:22:14.903
This is Cole's garrison.
They owe allegiance to me.

319
00:22:14.904 --> 00:22:16.530
This is no garrison.

320
00:22:17.531 --> 00:22:20.409
You must presume these men hold
allegiance only to themselves.

321
00:22:22.286 --> 00:22:24.288
[insects buzzing]

322
00:22:25.289 --> 00:22:27.248
[overlapping shouting]

323
00:22:27.249 --> 00:22:29.168
We cannot tarry here long.

324
00:22:32.421 --> 00:22:35.173
[♪ dramatic music playing]

325
00:22:35.174 --> 00:22:37.842
[people chattering]

326
00:22:37.843 --> 00:22:39.845
[chatter continues]

327
00:22:41.764 --> 00:22:44.141
[water sloshing]

328
00:23:01.116 --> 00:23:03.869
Good day. friend.
We seek food and shelter.

329
00:23:05.955 --> 00:23:08.998
Like many here gathered.
we are the dispossessed of the war.

330
00:23:08.999 --> 00:23:11.001
[Janos] You Riverfolk?

331
00:23:12.670 --> 00:23:16.173
I fucking hate Riverfolk.

332
00:23:16.841 --> 00:23:19.217
We hail from Sharp Point.

333
00:23:19.218 --> 00:23:20.970
Prince Aemond burned it
to the ground.

334
00:23:22.471 --> 00:23:23.889
[stammering]
W-w-with his d...

335
00:23:27.810 --> 00:23:30.312
- How'd you get out?
- We nearly didn't.

336
00:23:33.190 --> 00:23:34.984
As you can see.

337
00:23:36.694 --> 00:23:38.320
Hm.

338
00:23:46.912 --> 00:23:49.163
Well... [spitting]

339
00:23:49.164 --> 00:23:51.207
We're too many.

340
00:23:51.208 --> 00:23:52.585
Fuck off.

341
00:23:53.836 --> 00:23:55.337
I have some coin.

342
00:23:56.338 --> 00:23:58.007
[coins jingling]

343
00:24:09.977 --> 00:24:13.354
You can earn a tent
if you're ready to work.

344
00:24:13.355 --> 00:24:14.731
Have you got a trade?

345
00:24:14.732 --> 00:24:16.399
I have some knowledge
of herbs.

346
00:24:16.400 --> 00:24:18.860
and. uh. I can read a little.

347
00:24:18.861 --> 00:24:20.029
Mm.

348
00:24:21.071 --> 00:24:23.197
[laughter]

349
00:24:23.198 --> 00:24:24.782
Maybe you'll be useful.

350
00:24:24.783 --> 00:24:27.201
I have the command
around here.

351
00:24:27.202 --> 00:24:30.788
Oh. that much
is clear. my lord.

352
00:24:30.789 --> 00:24:32.458
Tangletongue
works the latrines.

353
00:24:33.751 --> 00:24:36.337
Collects piss for the tanners.
shit for the farmers.

354
00:24:37.880 --> 00:24:39.923
This one can help him.

355
00:24:39.924 --> 00:24:41.382
Separate buckets.

356
00:24:41.383 --> 00:24:44.218
Mix it up. they won't pay.

357
00:24:44.219 --> 00:24:47.305
I won't touch
the fucking latrines...

358
00:24:47.306 --> 00:24:49.390
J-Just do as they say.
Gregor.

359
00:24:49.391 --> 00:24:51.184
- For now. hm?
- I can read just as well as he can.

360
00:24:51.185 --> 00:24:53.561
Tangletongue and Mangleface.

361
00:24:53.562 --> 00:24:55.564
[laughter]

362
00:24:58.067 --> 00:24:59.901
- You'll be good together.
- I-It's not bad...

363
00:24:59.902 --> 00:25:01.654
- Don't fucking touch me.
- ...once you're used to it. brother.

364
00:25:03.405 --> 00:25:04.907
Come on.

365
00:25:07.451 --> 00:25:09.160
Come on.

366
00:25:09.161 --> 00:25:11.454
Fuck off!

367
00:25:11.455 --> 00:25:13.457
[people chattering]

368
00:25:19.755 --> 00:25:21.631
I think we'll have
a nice time here tonight.

369
00:25:21.632 --> 00:25:26.094
We'll make merry tonight.
It'll be better than Honeyholt.

370
00:25:26.095 --> 00:25:28.013
- [chuckles]
- [door closes]

371
00:25:36.480 --> 00:25:38.774
Wait.

372
00:25:45.781 --> 00:25:48.200
I need to inspect the goods.

373
00:25:56.667 --> 00:25:58.794
Go and fetch
some rosemary.

374
00:26:05.134 --> 00:26:06.635
[whispering] Come on.

375
00:26:08.470 --> 00:26:10.055
[nervous breathing]

376
00:26:13.142 --> 00:26:15.393
Don't touch her!
Take your hands off of her!

377
00:26:15.394 --> 00:26:17.354
[indistinct shouting]

378
00:26:18.313 --> 00:26:20.732
[screaming]

379
00:26:20.733 --> 00:26:22.735
[grunting]

380
00:26:25.320 --> 00:26:26.863
Get them out of here!
Get them out!

381
00:26:26.864 --> 00:26:29.533
Get your hands off my brother.
you Hightower...

382
00:26:30.325 --> 00:26:32.411
[high-pitched ringing]

383
00:26:38.000 --> 00:26:39.752
Ser Hugh Hammer. Your Grace.

384
00:26:41.378 --> 00:26:43.171
[Rhaenyra]
Ser Hugh. I assure you.

385
00:26:43.172 --> 00:26:45.924
when there is news of a house.
you will be sent for.

386
00:26:47.468 --> 00:26:50.928
I understand that Ser Ulf
is to be sent to Tumbleton.

387
00:26:50.929 --> 00:26:53.514
- He is.
- If it pleases Your Grace.

388
00:26:53.515 --> 00:26:55.893
I offer to take the watch
on Vermithor.

389
00:26:58.020 --> 00:27:00.229
Your wife is at Tumbleton.
is she not?

390
00:27:00.230 --> 00:27:01.814
Ser Ulf has no stake
in the matter.

391
00:27:01.815 --> 00:27:03.358
Send me. because I do.

392
00:27:04.359 --> 00:27:07.071
I will not tire of watching
when one I love is below.

393
00:27:10.783 --> 00:27:12.241
Take it in turn between you.

394
00:27:12.242 --> 00:27:14.702
Keep watch on the town
and on each other.

395
00:27:14.703 --> 00:27:16.329
You may take the first post.

396
00:27:16.330 --> 00:27:18.040
See that Ulf is alerted
to the plan.

397
00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:21.418
Your Grace.

398
00:27:22.211 --> 00:27:24.212
[bell tolling]

399
00:27:24.213 --> 00:27:27.883
[Townsfolk chattering]

400
00:27:29.551 --> 00:27:31.428
[townsperson]
Disgusting.

401
00:27:35.390 --> 00:27:37.059
What's it say?

402
00:27:40.437 --> 00:27:41.980
"Queen of Bastards."

403
00:27:43.190 --> 00:27:46.485
Hightower loyalists trying
to fight a war they lost.

404
00:27:50.572 --> 00:27:53.241
[♪ fiddle playing]

405
00:27:53.242 --> 00:27:55.910
So. he has returned.

406
00:27:55.911 --> 00:27:58.079
[all cheering]

407
00:27:58.080 --> 00:27:59.413
[laughter]

408
00:27:59.414 --> 00:28:01.249
- Come on!
- Come on.

409
00:28:01.250 --> 00:28:03.292
- Ah! Good evening. ser!
- Hey!

410
00:28:03.293 --> 00:28:06.838
Ulf. the Dragonlord!
Hey. hey.

411
00:28:06.839 --> 00:28:08.589
More god than man.

412
00:28:08.590 --> 00:28:12.009
Hey. will you honor your friends
with a round of drinks. my lord?

413
00:28:12.010 --> 00:28:14.220
The price keeps rising.
we can't keep up.

414
00:28:14.221 --> 00:28:16.097
- Tell him.
- For everyone.

415
00:28:16.098 --> 00:28:17.765
Hear that?

416
00:28:17.766 --> 00:28:21.937
- Drinks for everyone!
- [all cheering]

417
00:28:25.440 --> 00:28:27.358
- He broke my arm.
- That one broke my nose.

418
00:28:27.359 --> 00:28:29.152
- He attacked my sister.
- You call yourself soldiers. This is a disgrace.

419
00:28:29.153 --> 00:28:30.779
- The children are terrified.
- What is this?

420
00:28:32.489 --> 00:28:34.657
You said your men
were honorable.

421
00:28:34.658 --> 00:28:35.993
This one has sinned.

422
00:28:39.121 --> 00:28:41.289
I was billeted
at the smithy. my lord.

423
00:28:41.290 --> 00:28:44.125
But the smith didn't like it.

424
00:28:44.126 --> 00:28:46.503
Mayhaps he resents
the imposition.

425
00:28:47.546 --> 00:28:49.673
Or mayhaps he is loyal
to Rhaenyra.

426
00:28:50.632 --> 00:28:51.966
But he struck me.

427
00:28:51.967 --> 00:28:53.968
My lord.
Now. if it please you.

428
00:28:53.969 --> 00:28:55.428
we bear you no ill will.

429
00:28:55.429 --> 00:28:57.889
But this man went
to ravish my sister

430
00:28:57.890 --> 00:29:00.683
and then broke my wife's arm
when she tried to stop him.

431
00:29:00.684 --> 00:29:02.476
She is a weaver.

432
00:29:02.477 --> 00:29:04.313
We need what little she earns.

433
00:29:05.480 --> 00:29:07.815
- Is this true?
- [Garrick] No. my lord.

434
00:29:07.816 --> 00:29:09.400
- [Kat] Liar!
- Look at this woman's arm.

435
00:29:09.401 --> 00:29:11.402
- She attacked me.
- Is there no safety

436
00:29:11.403 --> 00:29:12.820
- in our houses anymore?
- She called me a cunt!

437
00:29:12.821 --> 00:29:14.489
I will have calm.

438
00:29:18.744 --> 00:29:21.412
- What is your name?
- Garrick. my lord.

439
00:29:21.413 --> 00:29:22.830
of Whitegrove.

440
00:29:22.831 --> 00:29:24.833
Garrick of Whitegrove.

441
00:29:25.918 --> 00:29:27.794
You have violated guest right.

442
00:29:28.503 --> 00:29:30.504
You have debauched yourself
upon a woman

443
00:29:30.505 --> 00:29:32.173
and injured another.

444
00:29:32.174 --> 00:29:34.217
Your punishment
will fit your crime.

445
00:29:34.218 --> 00:29:35.843
You will be gelded.

446
00:29:35.844 --> 00:29:39.180
[sighs] And you will have
your own arm broken.

447
00:29:39.181 --> 00:29:40.431
You may remain in my service.

448
00:29:40.432 --> 00:29:42.600
but trespass again.
and you will hang.

449
00:29:42.601 --> 00:29:45.186
My lord. I have a wife.

450
00:29:45.187 --> 00:29:47.438
Oh! My lord!

451
00:29:47.439 --> 00:29:48.898
- [guard] Come on!
- [Garrick] No!

452
00:29:48.899 --> 00:29:51.360
See them home.
Have a maester tend to their wounds.

453
00:29:52.402 --> 00:29:53.612
[Garrick] No!

454
00:29:54.613 --> 00:29:55.864
My lord!

455
00:29:57.282 --> 00:30:00.535
We must keep a firm grip.
Tensions are high.

456
00:30:01.536 --> 00:30:04.705
Lawlessness and disorder
claw at our gates.

457
00:30:04.706 --> 00:30:05.958
Yes. sire.

458
00:30:15.842 --> 00:30:17.301
[Rhaenyra] <i>I wish to see
all correspondence</i>

459
00:30:17.302 --> 00:30:19.387
between the Red Keep
and Ormund Hightower

460
00:30:19.388 --> 00:30:20.722
since my father's death.

461
00:30:21.431 --> 00:30:22.557
Your Grace.

462
00:30:25.560 --> 00:30:28.145
How much control
do the Hightowers

463
00:30:28.146 --> 00:30:29.939
exert over the Faith?

464
00:30:29.940 --> 00:30:34.068
Well. they endowed the building
of the Starry Sept

465
00:30:34.069 --> 00:30:36.237
and Oldtown was their seat for.

466
00:30:36.238 --> 00:30:39.156
well. centuries before
the Conquest.

467
00:30:39.157 --> 00:30:41.909
The Seven are as intrinsic
to the Hightower fabric

468
00:30:41.910 --> 00:30:44.996
as. well. dragons are
to House Targaryen.

469
00:30:44.997 --> 00:30:46.914
But control. I think not.

470
00:30:46.915 --> 00:30:49.960
The Faith is too proud
to allow such influence.

471
00:30:51.920 --> 00:30:54.506
The. uh. the High Septon
has refused to anoint me.

472
00:30:56.758 --> 00:31:00.137
The Faith clings tightly
to its separate powers.

473
00:31:03.098 --> 00:31:07.352
If I may be so bold
to ask Your Grace...

474
00:31:08.270 --> 00:31:09.687
does it matter?

475
00:31:09.688 --> 00:31:11.939
- Wh...
- Your Grace sits the throne.

476
00:31:11.940 --> 00:31:15.026
Your people have welcomed
you back as a liberator.

477
00:31:15.027 --> 00:31:16.569
Your dragons rule the skies.

478
00:31:16.570 --> 00:31:19.281
Are these not symbols
of power enough?

479
00:31:20.657 --> 00:31:23.242
Perhaps I could remove him.

480
00:31:23.243 --> 00:31:25.953
The monarch has ever had
some influence

481
00:31:25.954 --> 00:31:27.955
in the... the naming
of the High Septon.

482
00:31:27.956 --> 00:31:30.958
but to remove him altogether
would surely...

483
00:31:30.959 --> 00:31:33.962
incite the Faith.
and therefore the faithful.

484
00:31:36.131 --> 00:31:38.467
Unless you were
considering a more. uh...

485
00:31:40.635 --> 00:31:42.304
permanent removal.

486
00:31:44.306 --> 00:31:46.182
I never thought you
so bloodthirsty. Orwyle.

487
00:31:46.183 --> 00:31:48.225
- Ah.
- Rather impressed.

488
00:31:48.226 --> 00:31:49.810
Alas. no.

489
00:31:49.811 --> 00:31:51.854
Bring Ormund's letters
once you have collated them.

490
00:31:51.855 --> 00:31:55.566
There's been no word from
Prince Daemon on his progress?

491
00:31:55.567 --> 00:31:57.319
None as yet. Your Grace.

492
00:32:01.156 --> 00:32:03.157
[Caraxes bellowing]

493
00:32:03.158 --> 00:32:04.492
[Jeyne Arryn]
I had thought never to see you

494
00:32:04.493 --> 00:32:06.994
in the Vale again.
Prince Daemon.

495
00:32:06.995 --> 00:32:09.915
What after the tragic death
of your first wife.

496
00:32:11.458 --> 00:32:14.251
And yet I receive raven after raven
from my bannermen

497
00:32:14.252 --> 00:32:17.171
informing me of your progress
throughout my domain.

498
00:32:17.172 --> 00:32:18.547
[Daemon] Hm.

499
00:32:18.548 --> 00:32:21.051
Time heals even
the deepest of wounds.

500
00:32:23.095 --> 00:32:25.972
I am most delighted
to return. my lady.

501
00:32:28.350 --> 00:32:32.853
And who could ever fail to be
charmed by your... warmth.

502
00:32:32.854 --> 00:32:34.647
But I mustn't tarry.

503
00:32:34.648 --> 00:32:37.858
You promised the crown men
in return for a dragon.

504
00:32:37.859 --> 00:32:40.195
Now. you had your dragon.
yet we have no men.

505
00:32:42.197 --> 00:32:44.407
I should send babes.

506
00:32:44.408 --> 00:32:45.991
Prince Joffrey's dragon
was years away

507
00:32:45.992 --> 00:32:47.910
from being large enough
to defend the Vale.

508
00:32:47.911 --> 00:32:49.621
and Rhaenyra took
even that away.

509
00:32:50.539 --> 00:32:52.373
A less forbearing person

510
00:32:52.374 --> 00:32:54.375
might have seen
the crown's offering as an insult.

511
00:32:54.376 --> 00:32:57.211
- A pledge is a pledge.
- It was my understanding

512
00:32:57.212 --> 00:32:59.296
