761
00:49:48.639 --> 00:49:50.307
Clear the room.

762
00:50:05.406 --> 00:50:06.449
[door closes]

763
00:50:07.158 --> 00:50:08.325
What is this?

764
00:50:10.202 --> 00:50:11.453
The queen's justice.

765
00:50:11.454 --> 00:50:12.788
Who is he?

766
00:50:13.831 --> 00:50:16.249
And how did he come
to claim a wild dragon?

767
00:50:16.250 --> 00:50:18.626
Was he alone. or is...

768
00:50:18.627 --> 00:50:21.212
is he allied to Aemond
or to Ormund?

769
00:50:21.213 --> 00:50:22.755
I desired
the very same answers.

770
00:50:22.756 --> 00:50:24.507
but a dragon is not
a precise instrument.

771
00:50:24.508 --> 00:50:27.177
[scoffs]
What of Sheepstealer?

772
00:50:27.178 --> 00:50:29.345
Fled. Riderless.

773
00:50:29.346 --> 00:50:31.264
It is an act of madness
to claim a wild dragon.

774
00:50:31.265 --> 00:50:32.808
We are not like to see it again.

775
00:50:39.607 --> 00:50:42.776
I wanted to see him.

776
00:50:46.947 --> 00:50:50.993
I wanted to look on the one
who killed my son.

777
00:50:55.289 --> 00:50:56.916
To punish him yourself?

778
00:50:59.460 --> 00:51:01.670
But do you think
that would end your grief?

779
00:51:02.630 --> 00:51:04.256
I have served your interest.

780
00:51:15.643 --> 00:51:19.063
The gold you brought will
provide alms for the smallfolk.

781
00:51:20.272 --> 00:51:23.150
The City Watch trusts you.
You will entreat them to be patient.

782
00:51:24.485 --> 00:51:26.487
The crown will honor its debt...

783
00:51:27.488 --> 00:51:28.822
a little longer.

784
00:51:35.162 --> 00:51:36.330
I suppose...

785
00:51:37.665 --> 00:51:39.333
I should thank you.

786
00:51:48.551 --> 00:51:52.345
When what you've wrought
comes falling down about her ears.

787
00:51:52.346 --> 00:51:55.015
she'll return to her senses.

788
00:51:55.724 --> 00:51:57.309
Whose head is that?

789
00:52:01.188 --> 00:52:04.191
[♪ dramatic music playing]

790
00:52:37.057 --> 00:52:40.393
I have dispatched good men
to see your father's remains

791
00:52:40.394 --> 00:52:41.937
delivered to Oldtown.

792
00:52:50.321 --> 00:52:51.780
Viserys would have wished it.

793
00:52:54.617 --> 00:52:55.826
Thank you.

794
00:53:17.765 --> 00:53:19.016
[whispering] Here.

795
00:53:31.779 --> 00:53:33.280
Helaena.

796
00:53:38.786 --> 00:53:40.828
- [bell ringing]
- Clear the streets.

797
00:53:40.829 --> 00:53:42.330
Clear the streets!

798
00:53:42.331 --> 00:53:44.667
- [bell continues ringing]
- Observe the curfew!

799
00:53:46.210 --> 00:53:47.794
[people chattering
and shouting]

800
00:53:47.795 --> 00:53:49.213
All indoors!

801
00:53:51.131 --> 00:53:52.633
Clear the street!

802
00:53:55.135 --> 00:53:57.845
Stay home or hang!

803
00:53:57.846 --> 00:53:59.848
- Dragon!
- [dragon bellowing]

804
00:54:00.182 --> 00:54:01.308
Dragon!

805
00:54:20.494 --> 00:54:22.496
[bellowing]

806
00:54:26.834 --> 00:54:29.919
- Open your doors by order of the queen.
- [person shouting indistinctly]

807
00:54:29.920 --> 00:54:32.172
Here! Here!

808
00:54:33.340 --> 00:54:34.757
- With me.
- Up here.

809
00:54:34.758 --> 00:54:36.843
Get them out of their home!

810
00:54:36.844 --> 00:54:38.011
Who did this?

811
00:54:39.179 --> 00:54:41.139
Which traitor
stained these walls?

812
00:54:41.140 --> 00:54:42.890
Find the hand that
stained these walls.

813
00:54:42.891 --> 00:54:44.350
Scrub. Scrub!

814
00:54:44.351 --> 00:54:46.853
[Soldiers shouting]

815
00:54:46.854 --> 00:54:48.021
Bring them out!

816
00:54:52.025 --> 00:54:54.027
- [person screaming]
- [child crying]

817
00:55:09.251 --> 00:55:11.711
- Has he confessed?
- Not yet.

818
00:55:11.712 --> 00:55:14.089
I haven't done anything.
Please.

819
00:55:15.549 --> 00:55:16.717
Please.

820
00:55:17.843 --> 00:55:21.137
- Patience. my girl.
- [Tessarion purring]

821
00:55:21.138 --> 00:55:23.390
It won't be long before
we can fly again.

822
00:55:25.267 --> 00:55:27.185
[Tessarion grunting]

823
00:55:27.186 --> 00:55:29.645
I have warned you
against indulging in affection

824
00:55:29.646 --> 00:55:31.105
for that beast.

825
00:55:31.106 --> 00:55:33.399
[Tessarion bellowing]

826
00:55:33.400 --> 00:55:34.651
<i>Lykiri.</i>

827
00:55:35.778 --> 00:55:37.780
[Tessarion chittering]

828
00:55:39.907 --> 00:55:41.492
I know.

829
00:55:51.251 --> 00:55:52.669
You are a good boy.

830
00:55:54.338 --> 00:55:57.007
You speak kindly
and you say your prayers.

831
00:55:58.175 --> 00:56:00.009
I have raised you
in the light of the Seven.

832
00:56:00.010 --> 00:56:01.887
and the Father smiles upon you.

833
00:56:03.847 --> 00:56:05.933
But there is a taint
in your blood.

834
00:56:07.434 --> 00:56:10.269
The Targaryens
are a savage race.

835
00:56:10.270 --> 00:56:12.439
poor in intellect.
but rich in cunning.

836
00:56:14.191 --> 00:56:17.109
With dark spells.
they created abominations

837
00:56:17.110 --> 00:56:18.946
to subdue what was rightly ours.

838
00:56:22.908 --> 00:56:24.535
We are the superior men.

839
00:56:25.619 --> 00:56:27.954
But against that...

840
00:56:27.955 --> 00:56:29.705
[Tessarion growling]

841
00:56:29.706 --> 00:56:31.124
...we could not stand.

842
00:56:34.628 --> 00:56:36.463
[Tessarion growling. grunting]

843
00:56:39.675 --> 00:56:42.386
The gods have put you
to divine purpose. my boy.

844
00:56:43.428 --> 00:56:45.472
What purpose. sire?

845
00:56:46.807 --> 00:56:50.519
The brutes raise a woman
to the Iron Throne.

846
00:56:51.353 --> 00:56:52.562
A desecration!

847
00:56:52.563 --> 00:56:55.315
Where is reason?
Where is propriety?

848
00:56:56.316 --> 00:56:58.485
It was a blessing that you
came to ward in Oldtown.

849
00:56:59.486 --> 00:57:01.905
Your brothers are lost.
but you...

850
00:57:02.906 --> 00:57:05.032
remain a Hightower.

851
00:57:05.033 --> 00:57:07.451
raised in the shadow
of the Citadel.

852
00:57:07.452 --> 00:57:09.872
in the light of the Starry Sept.

853
00:57:14.877 --> 00:57:15.878
Now...

854
00:57:17.045 --> 00:57:18.672
you must be king.

855
00:57:23.844 --> 00:57:26.178
You would not wish. surely.

856
00:57:26.179 --> 00:57:28.681
for me to turn cloak
against my brothers.

857
00:57:28.682 --> 00:57:31.017
You will restore
our ancient order.

858
00:57:31.018 --> 00:57:33.937
Victory will be ours.
It is the will of the gods.

859
00:57:36.189 --> 00:57:37.733
I thought you let him go.

860
00:57:38.692 --> 00:57:40.443
A righteous king
must demonstrate

861
00:57:40.444 --> 00:57:42.570
he upholds many virtues.

862
00:57:42.571 --> 00:57:44.281
Honor. wisdom.

863
00:57:45.365 --> 00:57:48.367
- Justice. - He only acted when
our man attacked a woman.

864
00:57:48.368 --> 00:57:50.161
He laid hands on a Hightower.

865
00:57:50.162 --> 00:57:53.456
That soldier is an extension
of you. of the crown.

866
00:57:53.457 --> 00:57:55.041
Justice must be done.

867
00:57:55.042 --> 00:57:57.251
Is not mercy a kingly virtue?

868
00:57:57.252 --> 00:57:59.587
That sounds like something
your father would say.

869
00:57:59.588 --> 00:58:01.590
[Tessarion chittering]

870
00:58:03.884 --> 00:58:05.218
I'm sorry.

871
00:58:11.099 --> 00:58:13.101
[Tessarion chittering]

872
00:58:27.199 --> 00:58:30.077
I have risked much
and more to raise you up.

873
00:58:31.912 --> 00:58:33.956
Surely. you do not wish
to disappoint me.

874
00:58:42.589 --> 00:58:45.592
[♪ tense music playing]

875
00:58:50.931 --> 00:58:52.682
My lord.

876
00:58:52.683 --> 00:58:55.267
My lord. please. Please.

877
00:58:55.268 --> 00:58:57.812
No. please. I beg you.

878
00:58:57.813 --> 00:58:59.189
My lord.

879
00:59:00.941 --> 00:59:02.943
Please. I beg you.

880
00:59:04.820 --> 00:59:06.988
I have a family. my lord.

881
00:59:06.989 --> 00:59:08.699
I have a family.
Please.

882
00:59:10.117 --> 00:59:13.160
Please. please.
[whimpering]

883
00:59:13.161 --> 00:59:15.789
- [screaming]
- [Tessarion screeching]

884
00:59:16.540 --> 00:59:17.791
[exclaiming]

885
00:59:19.001 --> 00:59:22.004
[♪ tense music
continues playing]

886
00:59:31.304 --> 00:59:34.307
[♪ dramatic music playing]

887
00:59:48.905 --> 00:59:50.907
[Tessarion snarling]

888
00:59:57.831 --> 00:59:59.540
[screeching]

889
00:59:59.541 --> 01:00:01.543
[flames whooshing]

890
01:00:06.798 --> 01:00:08.340
And now we begin.

891
01:00:08.341 --> 01:00:10.259
[Tessarion snarling]

892
01:00:10.260 --> 01:00:12.262
[crunching]

893
01:00:17.350 --> 01:00:20.353
[♪ dramatic music playing]
